sentences: Memet Ali Alabora (born 25 November 1977) is a Turkish film and theatre actor.
In 1994, with support from his high school, Özel Boğaziçi Lisesi, Alabora founded a semi-professional theater.
At the same time, between 1995 and 1997, he worked as a reporter for the TV program A Takımı ("The A Team"), broadcast on ATV.
In 1999, he played the lead role in the film Kayıkçı ("Boatman"), a Turkish-Greek joint production.
Alabora is one of the founders of garajistanbul, a contemporary performing arts institution where he worked until May 2010.
In 2011 he was awarded a Tarzan of Manisa award.
In 2012 he financed, starred in and directed Mi Minör.
Alabora is an activist in favor of civil rights and the environment; in 2013 he supported the Gezi protests.
